= ⬡ QUARTER I GATHERING — The Prima Materia

*Theme:* First encounters with the work; establishing the foundations.

#hm-note[
  The gathering is not a lecture. It is a circle. Each student is heard. The
  headmaster facilitates but does not dominate. Use this time to observe the
  quality of the students' engagement and sincerity.
]

*Students share:*
- Their alchemical journals from Months 1–3.
- Their nature vigil observations from their chosen plant.
- The state of their Melissa maceration: color, scent, what has changed.
- One question that has genuinely unsettled or surprised them since beginning.

